---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Watchtower">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <p class="eyebrow">Watchtower</p>
      <h1>A clear view of cryptocurrency growth across decentralized networks.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Heimdall organizes on-chain data, price movements, and network health signals
        into a single watchtower for tracking the decentralized landscape as it evolves.
      </p>
      <div class="grid gateway-grid">
        <article class="card"><h3>1. Track</h3><p>Monitor price velocity, on-chain volume, and active address trends across Bitcoin, Ethereum, and emerging chains.</p></article>
        <article class="card"><h3>2. Compare</h3><p>Cross-reference growth signals between networks to spot rotations and adoption shifts before they hit headlines.</p></article>
        <article class="card"><h3>3. Validate</h3><p>Check validator health, attestation rates, and network decentralization metrics directly from node data.</p></article>
        <article class="card"><h3>4. Alert</h3><p>Get notified when growth patterns deviate from baseline or when network health indicators shift unexpectedly.</p></article>
        <article class="card"><h3>5. Archive</h3><p>Store historical chain state, price data, and network topology for long-term trend analysis and research.</p></article>
        <article class="card"><h3>6. Decentralize</h3><p>Connect directly to nodes rather than centralized APIs, keeping your data source independent and censorship-resistant.</p></article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .gateway-grid {
    margin-top: 42px;
  }
</style>
